name: DiagnosesUsedToIndicateSexualActivity
title: Diagnoses Used to Indicate Sexual Activity
purpose: (Clinical Focus: The purpose of this value set is to represent diagnoses indicating history of sexual activity.),(Data Element Scope: This value set may use a model element related to Diagnosis.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes concepts that represent a diagnosis of pregnancy, postpartum, sexually transmitted infection, conditions caused by sexually transmitted infections (e.g., inflammatory disease of ovary, fallopian tubes or uterus), symptoms following intercourse (e.g., bleeding), contraceptive use (e.g., adverse effect of contraceptive).),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes concepts that represent a diagnosis of congenital sexually transmitted infections; exposure to HIV virus; inconclusive serologic evidence of HIV.)
